sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant A as Anki
    participant I as __init__.py
    participant B as browser_utils.py
    participant F as field_visibility.py
    participant C as Config
    participant D as Editor DOM

    A->>I: Load add-on
    I-->>A: Register hooks and menu action

    U->>A: Open Browser
    A->>B: register_browser_instance(browser)
    B-->>A: Store current browser

    U->>A: Select note
    A->>F: editor_will_load_note(js, note, editor)
    F->>B: current_browser()
    F->>C: Read visibility config
    F-->>A: Return hide/reset JS
    A->>F: apply_field_visibility(editor)
    F->>C: Read visibility config
    alt Hiding is active
        F->>D: Hide non-allowed field containers
    else Hiding is disabled
        F->>D: Reset all field containers
    end

    U->>A: Click Show Fields
    A->>F: toggle_field_visibility(editor)
    F->>C: Add note type to field_visibility_disabled
    F->>D: Reset visibility
    F-->>A: Update button label

    U->>A: Click Hide Fields
    A->>F: toggle_field_visibility(editor)
    F->>C: Remove note type from field_visibility_disabled
    F->>D: Apply hide JS again
    F-->>A: Update button label
